00:15:32,557 --> 00:15:34,810
Michael. Michael Lee?

236
00:15:36,019 --> 00:15:37,979
Mr. P, please, can I go?

237
00:15:38,063 --> 00:15:41,024
I ain't eat no lunch
and my stomach making all these noises.

238
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:45,278
Look, I won't ever disrespect
your pencil again, I promise.

239
00:15:45,362 --> 00:15:49,116
- Zenobia, it wasn't about the pencil.
- Please, Mr. P.

240
00:15:57,874 --> 00:15:59,126
Come on, Mr. P.

241
00:16:00,335 --> 00:16:03,755
- Ok, ok, all right.
- All right.

242
00:16:03,922 --> 00:16:05,924
Just this one time, I'll make an exception.

243
00:16:07,926 --> 00:16:11,221
But next time, expect
to stay the full hour.

244
00:16:24,568 --> 00:16:26,528
- Why are you here?
- Came to say sorry.

245
00:16:26,653 --> 00:16:28,655
I didn't mean to get
all up in your face like that.

246
00:16:30,991 --> 00:16:32,242
I appreciate that, namond.

247
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:34,087
It takes courage
to admit when you're wrong.

248
00:16:34,411 --> 00:16:37,873
I can't understand - I've seen you
in Ms. Sampson's class, working.

249
00:16:37,998 --> 00:16:40,709
- Why can't you do the same in here?
- I mean to, I do.

250
00:16:41,668 --> 00:16:44,713
It's just the evil get in me
and before I know it, I go off.

251
00:16:47,215 --> 00:16:50,594
Well, tomorrow we'll
see if we can't do better.

252
00:16:51,261 --> 00:16:53,263
Can't tomorrow. Mrs. D put me out.

253
00:16:54,139 --> 00:16:56,099
I gotta bump. Later, Mr. P.

254
00:16:59,811 --> 00:17:01,438
If you can wait outside...

255
00:17:02,105 --> 00:17:03,648
It's ok. He can stay.

256
00:17:08,278 --> 00:17:09,362
Thank you.

257
00:17:10,822 --> 00:17:14,284
Mr. P, you know Michael
can't make it to detention.

258
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:16,161
I know he didn't. Now it's doubled.

259
00:17:16,286 --> 00:17:19,039
- He's got two days to serve.
- Nah, I mean, he can't.

260
00:17:19,331 --> 00:17:21,267
He got to go pick up
his little brother from school.

261
00:17:21,291 --> 00:17:23,668
He'll have to find
somebody else to do that.

262
00:17:26,254 --> 00:17:29,049
It ain't like that.
I mean, Michael would come if he could

263
00:17:29,132 --> 00:17:31,569
but wouldn't have nobody else
to pick up his little brother bug.

264
00:17:31,593 --> 00:17:34,512
You know, his mother, she on that stuff.

265
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:43,104
We walking home. You coming?

266
00:17:43,438 --> 00:17:46,900
No, I'm waiting on alpo.
Ms. Sampson got him doing detention.

267
00:17:46,983 --> 00:17:49,736
- You gonna be here till five o'clock.
- She a hard lady.

268
00:17:49,819 --> 00:17:53,573
- Don't ever give a brother no play.
- All right. I'll holla at you later.

269
00:17:53,657 --> 00:17:54,824
All right, yo.

270
00:17:57,869 --> 00:17:59,621
So you're not gonna be in the NBA?

271
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:02,207
Then it must be the NFL?

272
00:18:02,999 --> 00:18:05,418
I thought all the boys in class
were gonna join the pros.

273
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:07,212
Nah, that's just something we say.

274
00:18:08,129 --> 00:18:09,256
So what about you?

275
00:18:10,465 --> 00:18:14,511
- What do you wanna be when you grow up?
- I'm gonna own my own store.

276
00:18:15,095 --> 00:18:16,179
That's smart.

277
00:18:16,346 --> 00:18:18,014
You're gonna need
to know a lot of math.

278
00:18:22,477 --> 00:18:23,895
You left them in there.

279
00:18:26,856 --> 00:18:28,358
Hey, don't worry, Mr. P.
We got you.

280
00:18:28,692 --> 00:18:29,693
Hey, donut!

281
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:33,446
- Yo, yeah.
- Donut's crazy with cars.

282
00:18:33,530 --> 00:18:35,365
- He can open anything.
- Hey.

283
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:38,243
- What up, man?
- Yo, he locked his keys in there.

284
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:46,209
- It's ok, I can call AAA.
- Oh, no problem, chief.

285
00:19:29,252 --> 00:19:31,129
Feel the need to work them corners, huh?

286
00:19:32,964 --> 00:19:35,508
You don't need to be doing
what you're doing.

287
00:19:35,717 --> 00:19:37,510
I need to learn some shit on my own.

288
00:19:38,345 --> 00:19:40,013
I'm trying to help you, sherrod,

289
00:19:40,889 --> 00:19:42,432
but you making it so I can't.

290
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:44,602
I didn't even know the man
who beat on you, bubs.

291
00:19:44,934 --> 00:19:48,396
He was short of money on the corner.
I swear he wasn't nothing to me.

292
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,841
But when the shit start,
there's nothing to be done, right?

293
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:53,981
What would I have done
if he started whaling on you?

294
00:19:54,778 --> 00:19:56,321
Same kind of nothing, see?

295
00:19:57,572 --> 00:19:58,823
That's how the corners be.

296
00:20:00,450 --> 00:20:02,452
They going to use you up, sherrod.

297
00:20:08,124 --> 00:20:11,252
You welcome to stay tonight
but you ain't in school tomorrow morning,

298
00:20:12,128 --> 00:20:13,963
this partnership need to be done.

299
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:45,662
These two precincts are the bellwether
for the fifth.

300
00:20:45,912 --> 00:20:49,082
If you can take even 18%
out of carcetti in these,

301
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:51,543
it's a good guess
he won't have the numbers citywide.

302
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:55,213
Who are we ticketed with here?
The ndo, I hope...

303
00:20:55,338 --> 00:20:56,923
Because...

304
00:20:58,842 --> 00:21:02,512
This amid allegations that
high-ranking police officials intervened

305
00:21:02,595 --> 00:21:06,349
to have a veteran police detective removed
from the controversial case.

306
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:09,769
The braddock murder became
a focal point in the mayoral campaign

307
00:21:09,853 --> 00:21:13,690
when councilman Thomas carcetti alleged
the west Baltimore man was killed

308
00:21:14,065 --> 00:21:15,692
because he was a witness in the case.

309
00:21:16,234 --> 00:21:18,594
They were afraid the police would prove
what they most fear,

310
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:21,531
that fredro braddock was murdered
because he was a witness

311
00:21:21,698 --> 00:21:24,617
and the city failed to protect him.

312
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:27,328
It's on all three channels.

313
00:21:27,495 --> 00:21:30,039
And the sun and the post
are both calling for comment.

314
00:21:34,544 --> 00:21:37,630
My sources in the department say
rank-and-file officers are appalled

315
00:21:37,714 --> 00:21:40,800
- by this blatant political manipulation.
- Damn, turn it up.

316
00:21:41,217 --> 00:21:45,930
- Hey, greggs, you're famous.
- ..Is to remove a highly-decorated veteran

317
00:21:46,222 --> 00:21:49,142
with 15 years' experience
as a murder investigator without reason...

318
00:21:49,309 --> 00:21:51,227
- That'd be me.
- ..Replaced with a rookie

319
00:21:51,311 --> 00:21:53,313
yet to handle a single
homicide investigation...

320
00:21:53,396 --> 00:21:55,166
- That'd be you.
- ..Then we need to rethink...

321
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:57,817
The fuck I ever do to him?

322
00:22:01,154 --> 00:22:04,741
- You gonna make it too heavy, yo.
- It might work if we make it bigger.

323
00:22:05,116 --> 00:22:07,494
It'd work with balsa wood.
It's light and strong.

324
00:22:07,577 --> 00:22:09,245
Man, you so full of...

325
00:22:09,954 --> 00:22:11,164
Oh, shit.

326
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:18,922
Zombie master.

327
00:22:25,261 --> 00:22:26,679
Need to take us a little walk.

328
00:22:28,264 --> 00:22:29,599
Nah, I'm good here.

329
00:22:30,308 --> 00:22:32,560
Yo. Young 'uns need to move along.

330
00:22:34,771 --> 00:22:36,356
Sure, Chris, we'll bump.

331
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:46,032
- Yo, snoop, your sister in my class.
- What the fuck? You high, nigger?

332
00:22:48,117 --> 00:22:49,702
You boys be smoking that shit?

333
00:22:54,249 --> 00:22:55,667
Hearing good things about you.

334
00:22:56,251 --> 00:22:58,091
Say you straight up,
take care of your people,

335
00:22:58,294 --> 00:22:59,837
not begging no handouts.

336
00:23:01,047 --> 00:23:03,383
Motherfucker,
you hear the nigger talking to you,

337
00:23:03,466 --> 00:23:05,009
giving you praises and shit.

338
00:23:05,093 --> 00:23:07,804
- You standing here looking fucking stupid.
- Yo, chill.

339
00:23:09,806 --> 00:23:13,434
- Sometimes she get a little hot.
- I'm just saying the boy ain't right!

340
00:23:14,269 --> 00:23:16,604
Yo, we always in the market
for a good soldier.

341
00:23:17,146 --> 00:23:20,233
When we see one we like,
we take care of the situation -

342
00:23:20,817 --> 00:23:23,236
take him in, school him, make him family.

343
00:23:24,153 --> 00:23:25,673
And if you're with us, you're with us,

344
00:23:25,738 --> 00:23:27,740
just like we'd be with you all the way.

345
00:23:28,658 --> 00:23:29,867
You have a mind, you're in.

346
00:23:30,952 --> 00:23:32,996
Look, man. I already got a family -

347
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:36,249
my moms and my little brother.

348
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:37,834
Yeah, heard that.

349
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:40,253
But think on it.

350
00:23:44,841 --> 00:23:46,509
We'll be around if you need something.

351
00:24:01,316 --> 00:24:04,736
He saw me, yo. I knew it.
I knew Chris was asking Michael about me.

352
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:07,488
I knew it, man. I'm dead.

353
00:24:09,449 --> 00:24:11,242
- Yo, man, good looking-out.
- Yeah.

354
00:24:11,492 --> 00:24:13,119
- I thought he was gonna...
- I know.

355
00:24:13,411 --> 00:24:15,455
What he ask about me?
I know he asked about me.

356
00:24:15,538 --> 00:24:16,978
- What did you tell him?
- Calm down.

357
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:18,642
- It weren't even about you.
- Yo, for real,

358
00:24:18,666 --> 00:24:20,627
you need to tell me.
What did he ask you?

359
00:24:22,712 --> 00:24:25,548
Yo, you right, man.
Chris was all up in your business.

360
00:24:26,299 --> 00:24:28,593
He down on you for some deep shit, man.

361
00:24:28,926 --> 00:24:30,094
I don't even know what.

362
00:24:33,264 --> 00:24:35,141
Nah, I'm just fucking with you, man.

363
00:24:35,224 --> 00:24:36,934
He didn't even speak your name.

364
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:45,860
Oh, man.

365
00:24:49,739 --> 00:24:50,990
So, erv, what's next?

366
00:24:51,074 --> 00:24:53,076
Your officers gonna shoot
a couple of tourists?

367
00:24:53,493 --> 00:24:55,912
Maybe fly a helicopter into harbor place?

368
00:24:56,162 --> 00:24:59,707
What can we expect the last week
of my re-election campaign?

369
00:24:59,999 --> 00:25:01,959
Sir, I did what you
asked - no more, no less.

370
00:25:02,168 --> 00:25:06,172
- Hamsterdam - legalized drug zone?
- He takes responsibility for that.

371
00:25:06,255 --> 00:25:08,257
- The subpoenas all over town.
- That, too.

372
00:25:08,424 --> 00:25:11,678
The leak about the witness murder.
That was his shop too, right?

373
00:25:11,761 --> 00:25:14,055
- Hell, yeah.
- And now this last thing,

374
00:25:14,389 --> 00:25:17,517
transferring detectives off the case.

375
00:25:17,767 --> 00:25:19,102
What is that? What is that?

376
00:25:19,185 --> 00:25:21,437
- Scuttling the investigation.
- Yeah, right.

377
00:25:21,521 --> 00:25:24,148
- Yeah, that's awful. Jesus!
- Mr. Mayor, you asked me

378
00:25:24,232 --> 00:25:25,817
to slow that investigation down.

379
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:28,778
Subtle, ervin. Mm?

380
00:25:29,529 --> 00:25:31,197
You hold a few facts for a few weeks.

381
00:25:32,115 --> 00:25:34,200
You put a report or two in a desk drawer.

382
00:25:35,201 --> 00:25:37,453
But the transferring of people off a case?

383
00:25:37,787 --> 00:25:41,374
Look, you told me...
You specifically wanted me to not...

384
00:25:41,457 --> 00:25:43,793
Ervin, you may leave.

385
00:25:44,627 --> 00:25:48,464
- Mr. Mayor...
- That will be all, commissioner.

386
00:26:01,477 --> 00:26:04,647
No, I need a word or two
with your deputy, ervin.

387
00:26:17,827 --> 00:26:18,911
Have a seat.

388
00:26:27,170 --> 00:26:28,337
I tried to warn him.

389
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:30,882
If it leaked out
of homicide about the dead witness,

390
00:26:30,965 --> 00:26:32,845
why wouldn't it leak
that we bumped a detective?

391
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:35,011
Why didn't you come to us beforehand?

392
00:26:37,138 --> 00:26:38,848
I'm a loyal subordinate, Mr. Mayor,

393
00:26:40,183 --> 00:26:43,019
and ervin is a good man
working under considerable pressure.

394
00:26:43,227 --> 00:26:44,312
He's a hack.

395
00:26:44,562 --> 00:26:46,814
You're not bothered by
the pressure, deputy?

396
00:26:47,356 --> 00:26:48,608
Not in the least.

397
00:26:54,572 --> 00:26:56,407
I need you to make this go away, bill.

398
00:26:56,824 --> 00:26:58,618
I won't forget, believe me.

399
00:27:11,214 --> 00:27:14,050
Another thing -
slim Charles got up with me.

400
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:17,637
- Said the fat man want a sitdown.
- No. I did that already.

401
00:27:18,638 --> 00:27:21,390
Slim say the fat man knew
the card game was gonna get took.

402
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:23,059
He did, did he?

403
00:27:24,018 --> 00:27:25,019
Set it up.

404
00:27:25,895 --> 00:27:29,565
- Why you always be back here?
- Quiet. And I can see what comes.

405
00:27:30,233 --> 00:27:33,319
- But you out in the weather and shit.
- Don't like to speak in no rooms.

406
00:27:33,694 --> 00:27:36,656
- Yeah.
- Yo, you ain't staying long.

407
00:27:39,867 --> 00:27:42,411
So you know, I almost got that for you.

408
00:27:42,537 --> 00:27:45,998
- I just need a couple of days more.
- You can keep my money for now.

409
00:27:46,165 --> 00:27:49,085
- I got something needs doing.
- Anything, marlo, your call.

410
00:27:49,293 --> 00:27:53,089
Omar gonna come in your store,
stick it up, Rob you.

411
00:27:53,256 --> 00:27:55,591
You gonna call the police,
make a report.

412
00:27:56,551 --> 00:27:57,552
You feel me?

413
00:27:57,635 --> 00:28:00,221
Yeah, that'll work,
but you know when he get out,

414
00:28:00,346 --> 00:28:02,932
he's coming right at me.
I ain't scared or nothing.

415
00:28:03,057 --> 00:28:05,177
- I'm just saying, you know?
- He ain't gonna get out.

416
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:14,402
A man make bail on robbery.

417
00:28:16,153 --> 00:28:17,321
Make it no bail.

418
00:28:20,908 --> 00:28:24,287
If you have a problem,
like you can't make it to detention,

419
00:28:25,037 --> 00:28:26,205
you need to tell me.

420
00:28:26,956 --> 00:28:28,291
That's your responsibility.

421
00:28:28,791 --> 00:28:32,545
People will be more than willing
to help you out but it's up to you to ask.

422
00:28:35,339 --> 00:28:37,341
You can go back to the cafeteria...

423
00:28:38,676 --> 00:28:40,052
Or hang up here.

424
00:28:50,479 --> 00:28:52,815
Duquan, could you come here?

425
00:29:04,660 --> 00:29:07,914
I thought maybe you could help me out -
I packed too much.

426
00:29:29,143 --> 00:29:30,996
Take this down to the cafeteria
and get yourself something

427
00:29:31,020 --> 00:29:32,229
to drink from the machine.

428
00:29:33,356 --> 00:29:34,357
Thank you.

429
00:29:43,491 --> 00:29:45,242
Crystal, you got a second?

430
00:29:49,413 --> 00:29:50,623
What's up with duquan?

431
00:29:50,706 --> 00:29:52,959
I gave him some new clothes.
I was expecting...

432
00:29:53,042 --> 00:29:54,210
He might have lost them.

433
00:29:55,211 --> 00:29:56,420
That fast?

434
00:29:58,839 --> 00:30:00,049
It weren't that.

435
00:30:00,132 --> 00:30:02,802
His people take his clothes,
sell it on the corners.

436
00:30:03,219 --> 00:30:04,887
- You're kidding.
- No, sir.

437
00:30:05,054 --> 00:30:06,222
Everybody knows.

438
00:30:10,893 --> 00:30:14,397
Which brings me to what we're proposing -
different kids, different approaches.

439
00:30:14,522 --> 00:30:16,959
You tell us who we need to touch
at north Avenue to get the go-ahead.

440
00:30:16,983 --> 00:30:18,192
The puzzle palace?

441
00:30:18,651 --> 00:30:21,988
Look, if y'all still wanna
jump in and help, I'm fine with it.

442
00:30:22,530 --> 00:30:24,490
That's about all the ok
you need in my house.

443
00:30:26,492 --> 00:30:28,911
The stricker street situation
is waiting in the office.

444
00:30:30,121 --> 00:30:33,124
Neighborhood squabbles,

445
00:30:33,416 --> 00:30:34,917
and my babies bring it in here.

446
00:30:35,084 --> 00:30:38,546
Two fights yesterday - all because
the mothers can't get along.

447
00:30:39,422 --> 00:30:40,423
I gotta go.

448
00:30:40,506 --> 00:30:42,466
Mrs. Donnelly'll work out
the nuts and bolts.

449
00:30:44,552 --> 00:30:46,929
But just so you hear it, thank you.

450
00:30:47,638 --> 00:30:50,641
It'll be the only time anyone
in this system will think to say it.

451
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:57,606
- He's a good man. You need to protect him.
- Protect him?

452
00:30:57,773 --> 00:31:00,067
Principal withers just went out
on a limb for you,

453
00:31:00,151 --> 00:31:02,445
and in this system they know
how to handle a chainsaw.

454
00:31:03,738 --> 00:31:05,031
Excuse me?

455
00:31:05,781 --> 00:31:08,284
Anyone has a problem with what we're doing,
it's on him.

456
00:31:09,410 --> 00:31:12,163
So, you specified eighth-graders?

457
00:31:12,580 --> 00:31:16,625
We have 256 on roll.

458
00:31:16,792 --> 00:31:19,045
241 attend on a regular basis.

459
00:31:19,128 --> 00:31:22,173
Of those, 40 or so would fit your bill
of corner kids.

460
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:23,883
40?

461
00:31:25,968 --> 00:31:27,136
Pretty workable.

462
00:31:30,514 --> 00:31:33,059
- What would you suggest?
- Start with ten or so.

463
00:31:33,142 --> 00:31:34,769
Ms. Sampson has enough to get you going.

464
00:31:34,852 --> 00:31:36,145
One of them named namond Brice?

465
00:31:36,604 --> 00:31:37,646
Pick of the litter.

466
00:31:38,064 --> 00:31:40,264
But you'll have to wait.
He's on a three-day suspension.

467
00:31:50,785 --> 00:31:53,996
Remember when I was a cadet,
I was up here on a cadaver search.

468
00:31:54,413 --> 00:31:58,375
Instructor gets on the radio to say,
"we're looking for one body in particular.

469
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:04,048
"If you go grabbing everyone you see,
we'll be here all day," he says.

470
00:32:04,673 --> 00:32:06,175
Leakin park...

471
00:32:06,467 --> 00:32:08,469
Where west Baltimore brings out its dead.

472
00:32:08,844 --> 00:32:11,013
Not any more, from the look of things.

