sitting here if I didn't believe

712
00:48:13,016 --> 00:48:15,977
Clarence Royce wasn't truly committed
to this city and its people.

713
00:48:16,061 --> 00:48:18,813
- And crime in our neighborhood?
- That's another good point.

714
00:48:19,314 --> 00:48:21,941
But, lady, between you and me,

715
00:48:22,484 --> 00:48:25,684
I can tell from your voice you're black
and you can tell from my voice I'm white.

716
00:48:25,945 --> 00:48:27,405
So I gotta ask you,

717
00:48:27,739 --> 00:48:30,575
when do you think the last time
a white man voted for a black man

718
00:48:30,658 --> 00:48:32,619
when there was another
white man in the race?

719
00:48:32,702 --> 00:48:34,805
I don't know,
but you must really believe in him.

720
00:48:34,829 --> 00:48:37,582
Ain't that what I been saying?
He's just the best candidate.

721
00:48:38,208 --> 00:48:40,376
- So you'll go with my man?
- I'll think about it.

722
00:48:40,502 --> 00:48:42,587
That's great. Thank you for your time.

723
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:44,130
- Bye-bye.
- All right.

724
00:48:54,682 --> 00:48:56,768
- I have a hall pass.
- Yeah, good for you.

725
00:49:41,396 --> 00:49:43,314
- Mine's down.
- Attaboy.

726
00:49:45,900 --> 00:49:49,070
You need bodies, Lester? Here you go.

727
00:49:52,157 --> 00:49:55,910
We got a warrant and a teletype
for my boy Lex.

728
00:49:56,744 --> 00:49:59,706
So dead or alive, he's on file.

729
00:49:59,873 --> 00:50:01,833
And beyond that,
it's time for you to shine

730
00:50:01,916 --> 00:50:05,170
that mighty intellect of yours
on some real murders.

731
00:50:05,628 --> 00:50:07,505
Give up the hypotheticals and shit.

732
00:50:08,923 --> 00:50:10,341
Yeah, I suppose.

733
00:50:13,178 --> 00:50:16,890
This is my issue - crime, and I understand
completely what you're saying.

734
00:50:17,390 --> 00:50:19,618
And if you give me the opportunity,
I will be able to do something

735
00:50:19,642 --> 00:50:22,604
to help you out and, you know,
other people in this neighborhood.

736
00:50:27,817 --> 00:50:30,737
Mr. Ricks, thank you for your time
and for your attention.

737
00:50:30,945 --> 00:50:32,655
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

738
00:50:33,907 --> 00:50:36,784
Pretty brazen, shaking hands
with the enemy in broad daylight.

739
00:50:38,203 --> 00:50:40,747
- Werner's deli this isn't.
- Definitely not.

740
00:50:41,122 --> 00:50:43,583
Though here you are, councilman,
leaving no door unopened.

741
00:50:43,708 --> 00:50:45,210
Shoe leather - our secret weapon.

742
00:50:45,418 --> 00:50:47,629
You surprised me.
You've made this a horse race.

743
00:50:47,962 --> 00:50:51,341
So what makes me think you didn't
just happen by and find us here?

744
00:50:54,552 --> 00:50:56,179
Watkins is breaking with the mayor.

745
00:50:56,971 --> 00:50:58,097
How do you know?

746
00:50:59,015 --> 00:51:00,016
I know.

747
00:51:00,433 --> 00:51:02,810
I've carried the mayor's water
because I had to, councilman.

748
00:51:02,977 --> 00:51:04,771
I'd love to see some
new blood in this city.

749
00:51:05,313 --> 00:51:09,525
And I'd love the chance to do the right thing
for this police department for a change.

750
00:51:29,337 --> 00:51:31,422
Wait until he turns the corner.

751
00:51:35,551 --> 00:51:37,887
District office for Watkins -
gilmore street.

752
00:51:38,471 --> 00:51:39,931
And fuck them red lights, man.

753
00:51:47,689 --> 00:51:50,191
Not a place you expect
to find any gangsters -

754
00:51:51,150 --> 00:51:52,610
police, for that matter.

755
00:51:54,362 --> 00:51:57,824
- Heard you knew something I didn't.
- Told you before,

756
00:51:58,324 --> 00:52:00,702
I make it my business
to keep an ear to the ground.

757
00:52:01,202 --> 00:52:03,162
I make it my business to do business.

758
00:52:03,413 --> 00:52:05,373
We doing business, or are we just talking?

759
00:52:05,832 --> 00:52:07,166
And if it's talk, I'm-a walk.

760
00:52:07,250 --> 00:52:08,668
I heard the people pulling security

761
00:52:08,751 --> 00:52:11,462
at the card game weren't too keen
on their wages.

762
00:52:12,630 --> 00:52:14,066
I figured it was only a matter of time

763
00:52:14,090 --> 00:52:16,801
before they found a way
to get their due compensation.

764
00:52:17,719 --> 00:52:19,053
And you didn't think to tell me?

765
00:52:19,721 --> 00:52:22,015
A man learns best when he get burned.

766
00:52:23,266 --> 00:52:25,026
How do I know you
ain't making this shit up?

767
00:52:25,184 --> 00:52:27,603
You don't. Things happen on the street.

768
00:52:28,479 --> 00:52:29,981
Proof is hard to come by.

769
00:52:34,694 --> 00:52:36,738
Go ahead, open it.

770
00:52:41,909 --> 00:52:44,746
Off the street, there's all kind of proof.

771
00:52:45,330 --> 00:52:49,917
They planning on executing those Friday -
time it with the election, I guess,

772
00:52:50,460 --> 00:52:54,422
show they doing their job, cleaning
up the city, taking down a kingpin.

773
00:52:55,256 --> 00:52:56,466
How did you come by this?

774
00:52:56,549 --> 00:52:59,427
Told you before, I keep
my ear to the ground.

775
00:52:59,761 --> 00:53:02,430
- What are you gonna do with it?
- Maybe nothing.

776
00:53:03,348 --> 00:53:05,391
Charlie's not part of the co-op.

777
00:53:07,185 --> 00:53:09,062
Or maybe I tip him for a fee.

778
00:53:10,605 --> 00:53:13,566
What do you think a man
with a whole lot of money would pay

779
00:53:14,233 --> 00:53:15,443
for his freedom?

780
00:53:17,153 --> 00:53:19,364
You know, lately...

781
00:53:20,531 --> 00:53:23,076
I come to find out someone trying
to take pictures on me.

782
00:53:23,451 --> 00:53:25,745
- Pictures?
- Video.

783
00:53:26,788 --> 00:53:28,790
You heard anything about me
through your travels?

784
00:53:30,625 --> 00:53:32,210
Had no incentive to listen.

785
00:53:36,214 --> 00:53:37,465
You do now.

786
00:53:52,814 --> 00:53:57,902
It's one thing to sit out the primary. It's
another for me to turn on Clarence Royce.

787
00:53:58,778 --> 00:54:00,905
- Granted.
- And if I did jump,

788
00:54:01,322 --> 00:54:03,074
why not land behind Tony gray?

789
00:54:03,991 --> 00:54:05,910
At least he's from my side of the tracks.

790
00:54:06,327 --> 00:54:07,453
Tony can't win.

791
00:54:07,912 --> 00:54:08,913
I can.

792
00:54:11,374 --> 00:54:15,837
Look, the truth is, whatever I can do
for you, the mayor can match or double.

793
00:54:16,129 --> 00:54:20,049
I have a pretty good grass-roots organization
but nothing even close to his kind of money.

794
00:54:20,550 --> 00:54:22,677
Now, I'll ticket up with anyone
you want me to.

795
00:54:22,844 --> 00:54:25,805
I know you want Daniels in the 11th
and Stokes in the 10th.

796
00:54:26,347 --> 00:54:28,808
I'll keep away from any tickets
you think I might harm.

797
00:54:29,350 --> 00:54:32,061
I know I'm not everyone's idea
of a bargain on your side of town.

798
00:54:33,062 --> 00:54:35,898
But right now, a week from the primary,

799
00:54:36,566 --> 00:54:39,360
the fact is, Royce and I both need you.

800
00:54:40,319 --> 00:54:41,529
After the election,

801
00:54:41,654 --> 00:54:44,157
the equation changes
for him but not for me.

802
00:54:44,699 --> 00:54:47,201
I'm a white mayor in a majority-black city,

803
00:54:47,368 --> 00:54:49,537
and if I'm gonna do
anything - and, delegate,

804
00:54:49,620 --> 00:54:51,497
I am so serious about fixing this city -

805
00:54:51,581 --> 00:54:53,666
I'm gonna have to govern by consensus.

806
00:54:54,250 --> 00:54:56,810
If you support me, you will have
a voice within my administration

807
00:54:56,836 --> 00:54:58,629
simply because I'm gonna need it.

808
00:55:02,592 --> 00:55:04,385
Last poll that Clarence showed me,

809
00:55:05,219 --> 00:55:06,554
he was up by seven points.

810
00:55:08,222 --> 00:55:10,558
Bullshit. I'm within four.

811
00:55:16,272 --> 00:55:19,233
- You won't be needing that.
- I know.

812
00:55:21,944 --> 00:55:23,738
- Here?
- Yeah, here.

813
00:56:02,235 --> 00:56:03,444
Dag.

814
00:56:03,611 --> 00:56:05,571
Yo, turn it off - the bulb might
have got too hot.

815
00:56:06,614 --> 00:56:07,854
Or the battery's dying.

816
00:56:09,784 --> 00:56:10,785
We should go back.

817
00:56:14,997 --> 00:56:18,000
- Yo, man, it stinks, man.
- Ain't like it was.

818
00:56:32,974 --> 00:56:34,600
See, he ain't move.

819
00:56:38,062 --> 00:56:39,188
Yeah.

820
00:56:40,773 --> 00:56:42,441
Blood still stuck to his hair.

821
00:56:43,317 --> 00:56:44,527
He dead?

822
00:56:45,736 --> 00:56:46,737
He dead.

823
00:56:47,989 --> 00:56:48,990
Lextoo?

824
00:56:49,574 --> 00:56:51,158
He dead. They all is.

825
00:56:52,326 --> 00:56:53,327
Feel better?

826
00:56:54,829 --> 00:56:56,163
Donut wrong, yo.

827
00:56:57,123 --> 00:56:58,499
Ain't no special dead.

828
00:57:01,919 --> 00:57:03,588
There's just dead.

